      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING GRYLLIS (3) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 4 lengths at Nowra in a handy 20.59. Has a low draw and goes well over this trip. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Ideally placed to take this out. BANJO'S EXPRESS (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (20.77) at Nowra behind Maybe Next Week in a Free For All. Bold showing expected. CANYA SUPERSONIC (2) boasts a consistent overall record including 24 wins from 86 starts, but missed the frame latest when fourth (19.35) over 340m at Bulli. Super consistent and can feature with the right run. GOODBYE MATE (4) jumps at a shorter distance and still warrants respect.",
